# 🟢 Optimal Approach (Dynamic Programming)

### Observation

The recursive solution computes the same states repeatedly.

Example

```
countWays(7)

calls

countWays(6)

countWays(5)

countWays(4)

Again countWays(5)

Again countWays(4)
```

Many repeated calculations.

Store answers once.

---

## DP State

```
dp[i]

=

Number of ways to tile i × m floor
```

---

## Transition

```
dp[i]
=
dp[i-1]
+
dp[i-m]
```

---

## Base Cases

```
i < m

dp[i]=1
```

```
i==m

dp[i]=2
```

---

## Code

```python
class Solution:
    def countWays(self, n, m):

        dp = [0] * (n + 1)

        for i in range(n + 1):

            if i < m:
                dp[i] = 1

            elif i == m:
                dp[i] = 2

            else:
                dp[i] = dp[i - 1] + dp[i - m]

        return dp[n]
```

